  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop, update, prepare 3D model and shop drawings for submission to the clients and construction using BIM software.</li><li>Maintain up-to-date 3D model according to the latest information and audit regularly.</li><li>Generate 2D drawing, documentation, and As-Built BIM model and detailing submission based on company standard.</li><li>Work in accordance with project scope and schedule, and ensure accuracy.</li><li>Ensure models and/or drawings produced to comply with applicable codes, standards and specifications.</li><li>Work in accordance with checking procedures in delivering high-quality models, drawings and/or drawings.</li><li>Co-ordinate with sub-contractors to exchange latest updates and models.</li><li>Any other duties assigned by superior.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Architecture, Civil Engineering, Construction, or a related field.</li><li>Preferably with a minimum of 2-3 years relevant working experience in the contractor, consultant or outsource service provider.</li><li>Extensive hands-on experience with BIM modeling and implementation, often with a focus on large-scale infrastructure.</li><li>Proficient in Revit (Architecture/ MEP/ Structure).</li><li>Able to perform tasks accurately and reliably with excellent attention to detail.</li></ul>",
